      "content": "it's more than just a \"gut feeling\" though. it's almost like I can hear the actual pitch change. like, if he's telling the truth, the audio of his voice feels smooth and stable, but when he's lying, there's this sharp, micro-tonal dissonance. it's like a frequency clash. do u think there could be a physical, acoustic reason why a lie would change the actual resonance of a person's voice?",
